This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with salient object detection using deep neural networks. Additionally, it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it involves data-driven strategies and multi-task learning schemes. The paper also discusses the use of graph Laplacian regularization, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of fully convolutional neural networks suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
